        <h2 class="text-center">Programs</h2>
        <hr>
        <h3>Socials</h3>
        <p>
          We are committed to retaining members and making sure everyone feels like part of the SHPE familia. Social events are planned by the social committee to be as inclusive and as fun as possible. Some past events include: BBQs, potlucks, study lockdowns, movie night, and fiestas. Annual tradtional events include: a visit to Hardy's Reinder Ranch for their fall corn maze, a Thanksgiving dinner (hosted before winter break), a Christmas gift exchange, a Christmas gingerbread house making and spring paintballing. By getting involved, you too can be a part of planning SHPEâ€™s next great event. Make sure to check the <%= link_to 'Facebook General Body Page', 'https://www.facebook.com/shpe.uiuc' %> for upcoming SHPE social events!
        </p>
        <h3>PartnerSHPE</h3>
        <p>
          The PartnerSHPE program works to aid its underclassmen members in finding meaningful upperclassmen mentors to help guide them in their academic and professional development. The program is a competition in which each mentor/mentee team gains points in order to win a prize at the end of the school year. To earn points, a mentor and mentee team must participate in activities together such as studying together, attending PartnerSHPE Socials together, or attending career fairs together. These moments must have photographic evidence to gain the points associated with them.
        </p>
        <p> 
          More information about the PartnerSHPE Challenge Rules can be found 
          <%= link_to 'HERE', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1XGL_5_jxW6FklaE1p0ok5YKVnVzwDjrGEhhYxc5ZP_o/edit?usp=sharing' %>
        </p>
        <p>
          Please contact the social chair if you are interested in becoming a mentor or a mentee.
        </p>
        <h3>MemberSHPE Challenge</h3>
        <p>
          SHPE UIUC loves having our members actively involved in our chapter. We pride ourselves in making sure our members are well rounded academically and professionally. We reward those members which are the most active in all SHPE events dealing with academics, professional development, community service, and chapter development. The top three most active members win a prize at the end of the school year.
        </p>
